s, and communities in the throes of cataclysmic change. Jalal brings to life the people, locales, and events that inspired Manto's fiction, which is characterized by an eye for detail, a measure of wit and irreverence, and elements of suspense and surprise. In turn, she mines these writings for fresh insights into everyday cosmopolitanism in Bombay and Lahore, the experience and causes of partition, the postcolonial transition, and the advent of the Cold War in South Asia. The first in-depth look in English at this influential literary figure, The Pity of Partition demonstrates the revelatory power of art in times of great historical rupture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aAuthors, Urduy20th centuryvBiography. 0aAuthors, Urduy20th centuryxBiography. 0aAuthors, Urduy20th century. 0aAuthors, Urdu. 0aIndia - History - Partition, 1947. 0aIndia-Pakistan Conflict, 1947-1949. 0aLiterature. 0aManoto, Saaadat oHasan - Criticism and interpretation. 0aManoto, Saaadat oHasan - Political and social views. 0aManoto, Saaadat oHasan. 0aNarration (Rhetoric) - Political aspects - South Asia - History - 20th century. 0aNarration (Rhetoric)xPolitical aspectsxSouth AsiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aNarration (Rhetoric)xPolitical aspectszSouth AsiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aNarration (Rhetoric)xPolitical aspects. 0aPolitical and social views. 0aShort stories, UrduxHistory and criticism. 0aShort stories, Urdu. 0aSouth Asia - History - 20th century. 0aSouth Asia - In literature. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066258008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton eBook Packa